text: Ordered teh c ping siew dai here. They used ice kacang milk for teh c here. This has been the worst teh c I have drank.

Worst service staff ever. He confronted me loudly when he mistakenly thought I had underpaid him. Walked away and pretend as if nothing happened when found that it was his problem. Not apologetic.

I have been buying rice noodles/rice/kuey teow, etc. from this store. Today I packed it as usual. What is very disappointing is that the fried rice is already smelly and sour. I thought it would be okay to eat some fried rice noodles, but it turned out to be the same smelly and sour. It was probably only two or three hours after I bought it. Normally, it is not bad at all. This time it is smelly and sour. I think they sold it overnight...
